**File:** `agent/Dockerfile.agent` — **[NEW]**

```dockerfile
# OpsTron Log Forwarding Agent
# Lightweight container — runs on USER'S machine alongside their services
# Published to Docker Hub as opstron/agent:latest

FROM python:3.12-slim

WORKDIR /app

# Only install what the forwarder needs — not the full OpsTron stack
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir docker==7.1.0 requests==2.32.3

COPY opstron_forwarder.py /app/forwarder.py

# Health check so Docker knows the container is alive
HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=5s --retries=3 \
    CMD python -c "import requests; requests.get('http://localhost:8080/health', timeout=3)" || exit 1

CMD ["python", "/app/forwarder.py"]
```

